This week's One Good Thing is a surprising laundry tip that comes from one of Maxwell's friends in the theater business — since they have so many opportunities to put on the same costumes, but need to remove those annoying odors that get caught over time. Read more at the link in bio. #OneGoodThingAtHome

Read more at the link in bio. #OneGoodThingAtHome

node.text:

(Image & Home: @saimhin_so)

node.text:
@Jessicamalatyrivera, infectious disease epidemiologist and science communication lead at the @covidtrackingproject, has made a lovely temporary home in this California craftsman bungalow for her family. “The biggest challenge was knowing that we were only going to be in this home for one year, during the pandemic. I knew I couldn’t do the kinds of personal touches — fresh paint, new window treatments — that I would have done if we were staying a while longer. It was really important to me to make it as homey and as familiar as possible for all of us, especially the kids, without breaking the bank,” says Jessica. See how she did it and read more from our Healthy Home Issue at the link in bio. 

 (Images: @kaibyrd_; Home: @jessicamalatyrivera)
